## 4. CORE MECHANICS

### 4.1 Claim (Zone Creation)

**What:** Player runs a closed GPS loop around any area. That territory becomes theirs.

**How It Works:**
- Open app while running
- Run any closed path (circle, square, irregular boundary around a location)
- Minimum loop size: 0.5 km (to prevent garage-claiming)
- Maximum speed: 14 km/h (automatic stop if exceeded)
- Return to start point: GPS geofence detects closure
- **Result:** Zone created, player's color assigned, zone name auto-generated or player-named

**Zone Properties:**
- **Owner:** User who claimed it
- **Zone Color:** Assigned to user profile (can customize)
- **Zone Health:** Starts at 100%
- **Geometry:** Exact GPS boundary of the loop
- **Claimed At:** Timestamp
- **Current Streak:** Days defended without break
- **Size:** Square km or radius equivalents
- **Name:** Location name (if landmark) or user-assigned

**Gameplay Implications:**
- Bigger loops = harder to defend, larger territory
- Popular spots create competition (multiple players want same area)
- Iconic landmarks create prestige value

---

### 4.2 Attack (Territorial Theft)

**What:** Rival runs through your zone boundary. Every km they cover reduces your zone health.

**How It Works:**

**Attack Initiation:**
- Attacker opens app and runs
- Enters target zone boundary (GPS geofence detection)
- App shows "Zone detected: [Owner Name] - [Zone Name]"
- Real-time notification sent to **defender** (if online) and queued if offline
- **Zone status changes to "Under Attack"**

**Attack Progress:**
- Every 0.1 km attacker covers = 1% zone health reduction
- Attacker must cover **full boundary distance** to steal
  - 5 km boundary = attacker needs 5 km attack = 100% health drain = zone stolen
- Attacker can pause/stop mid-attack (progress saved for return attempt)
- Attack window: Persistent until completion OR defender restores health

**Attack Success Condition:**
- Zone health reaches 0% → Zone ownership transfers to attacker
- Zone color changes to attacker's color
- Defender's name removed from zone
- Attack logged in territory history

**Attack Failure Scenarios:**
- Defender runs the same loop boundary during attack → **health restored**
- Defender runs extra distance beyond loop → health bonus (up to 120%)
- Attacker exceeds 14 km/h → **attack resets**, progress lost
- 7 days pass without attacker returning → Attack expires, progress lost

**Notifications:**
- **Defender (real-time):** "Rohit is attacking your Dadar zone! 40% health remaining"
- **Attacker (real-time):** "You've covered 2.5 km of Rohit's zone. 50% until capture"
- **Both:** "Rohit stole your Dadar zone!" (if successful)

**Strategic Depth:**
- Attacker decides: finish now or come back later?
- Defender decides: defend now or lose the zone?
- Both races against game systems (decay, streaks)

---

### 4.3 Defend (Zone Restoration)

**What:** When under attack or losing health, player runs their own zone loop to restore health.

**How It Works:**

**Defend Activation:**
- Player receives notification: "[Rival Name] is attacking [Zone Name]"
- Player opens app → sees zone on map, shows current health %
- Player runs the same loop boundary (can start anywhere on boundary, must complete full circuit)
- GPS validates: user covers minimum 90% of original loop distance (slight variation allowed)
- Every km covered = 5% health restoration (minimum)

**Defense Success:**
- Zone health restored toward 100%
- If health was at 50% and player runs 5km boundary = +25% health = 75% total
- If health was at 90% and player defends = caps at 100%
- **Streak continues** (defined below)

**Defense During Attack:**
- Special case: While rival is mid-attack, defender runs same loop
- **Head-to-head mechanic:** Both are running simultaneously
- Whoever completes more of the boundary wins the contested km
  - Defender restores health for their % covered
  - Attacker's progress reduced by defender's %
- Creates real-time competitive tension

---

### 4.4 Decay (Entropy System)

**What:** Zones slowly lose health if not maintained. Forces daily engagement.

**How It Works:**

**Decay Schedule:**
- Every 24 hours: 2% zone health loss (if no activity)
- Every 48 hours: 4% additional loss (cumulative)
- Every 72 hours: 6% additional loss (cumulative)
- **Total after 72 hours:** 12% health loss with zero runs

**Decay Mechanics:**
- Decay pauses if player runs their zone boundary (any zone)
- Running ANY zone boundary → restarts decay timer for ALL zones
- Longer streak = slower decay rate
  - 7-day streak: -1.5% per day
  - 30-day streak: -0.5% per day
  - Break streak: returns to default -2% decay

**Game Design Purpose:**
- Ensures daily motivation (must run to maintain territory)
- Prevents "own it forever" passive gameplay
- Creates urgency without artificial timers
- Rewards consistency through streak decay reduction

---

### 4.5 Streak System (Consistency Reward)

**What:** Consecutive days of running a zone boundary. Longer streaks grant zone stability.

**How It Works:**

**Streak Tracking:**
- Day 1 run: Streak = 1
- Day 2 run: Streak = 2
- ...
- Day 30 run: Streak = 30
- **Miss one day:** Streak resets to 0

**Streak Benefits:**
| Streak Days | Zone Health Boost | Decay Reduction | Visual Badge |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1–3 days | +0% | -2% / day (normal) | 🔥 (bronze) |
| 4–7 days | +5% | -1.5% / day | 🔥🔥 (silver) |
| 8–14 days | +10% | -1% / day | 🔥🔥🔥 (gold) |
| 15–30 days | +15% | -0.5% / day | 👑 (platinum) |
| 30+ days | +20% | -0.25% / day | 💎 (diamond) |

**Streak Loss:**
- Miss running any day → all streaks reset to 0
- Grace period: None (harsh penalty encourages daily habit)
- Comeback: Run next day = streak restarts at 1

**Psychological Design:**
- Fear of losing streak = addiction
- Visual badges show competence to friends
- 14-day mark = habit formation + visible status
- 30-day mark = elite status in friend group

---

### 4.6 The 14 km/h Speed Cap (Trust Mechanism)

**What:** No input tracked above 14 km/h. Cannot cheat with vehicles.

**How It Works:**

**GPS Validation:**
- App continuously monitors GPS speed during run
- If speed > 14 km/h:
  - **Tracking pauses**
  - No km credited
  - No zone claimed/attacked/defended
  - Message: "Slow down—cycling/vehicles don't count"
  
- If speed drops below 14 km/h again:
  - **Tracking resumes**
  - Km resume from pause point

**Why 14 km/h?**
- ~8.7 mph = elite runner pace (~7-minute mile)
- Sustainable by strong runners, impossible by casual joggers with cycles
- Most cycles travel 18–25 km/h (clear enforcement)
- All vehicles exceed this (cars, bikes, scooters)
- Accessible to aspiring runners (not hobbyist-only)

**Trust Guarantees:**
- Every meter on map = earned on foot
- Leaderboards are honest
- Zones represent real running effort
- No pay-to-win zone claiming with vehicles

**Edge Cases:**
- Downhill sprints → App allows 14 km/h ±0.5 buffer (brief overages allowed)
- Drafting/wind assistance → Tracked honestly (not penalized)
- Stroller pushing → Works fine (speed stays under 14 km/h)

