## 15. APPENDIX: GLOSSARY & DEFINITIONS

| Term | Definition |
|---|---|
| **Zone** | GPS-bounded territory claimed by running a closed loop. Identified by owner, boundary, health %, streak |
| **Claim** | Act of creating a new zone by running a closed GPS loop |
| **Attack** | Running through rival's zone boundary, reducing their zone health |
| **Defend** | Running your own zone loop to restore health during attack |
| **Health %** | Zone vitality (0–100%). At 0%, zone stolen. Reduced by attacks, decay, inactivity |
| **Streak** | Consecutive days of running any zone loop. Breaks if player misses one day |
| **Decay** | Automatic health loss (-2% per day) if zone not run/defended for 24h |
| **14 km/h Rule** | GPS speed cap. Tracking pauses if speed exceeds 14 km/h. No input credited above this threshold |
| **Squad** | Group of 2+ players who coordinate territory & compete together |
| **War Room** | AI coach feature providing threat detection, zone recommendations, weekly reports |
| **Prestige** | Social value of zone (landmark zones worth more than random parks) |
| **Territory Perimeter** | Full GPS distance around zone boundary. Required to fully attack/defend |
| **MAU** | Monthly Active Users (users with 1+ activity in 30-day period) |
| **DAU** | Daily Active Users (users with 1+ activity on specific day) |
| **ARPU** | Average Revenue Per User (monthly) |

